## 32. Speech to Text (STT) — The Concept

Speech-to-text converts audio into a string of words. The engine must:

1. Segment the audio into phonemes or spectral features.
2. Match those features against a language model.
3. Return the most likely word sequence.

The Scheme interface:

```scheme
;; Speech-to-text: transcribe audio to a string
(speech/listen audio-buffer)
```

*[needs: speech/listen verb — STT engine or cloud integration]*  
<!-- BUILD: speech/listen — integrate STT model or API; return string -->

The verb accepts an audio buffer (from a microphone or file) and returns a string. This is also flagged as an engine gap.

---

## 33. A Live Transcription

Capture audio from the microphone and transcribe it:

```scheme
;; Listen and transcribe
(define captured-audio (record 3.0))  ; record 3 seconds
(speech/listen captured-audio)
```

*[needs: record verb + speech/listen]*  
<!-- BUILD: record verb — capture audio from mic; speech/listen — STT -->

The output is a string of the words spoken into the microphone.

