## 35. A Voice Command

Transcribe a short command and branch on the result:

```scheme
;; Voice command: \"play\" or \"stop\"
(define captured (record 2.0))
(define command (speech/listen captured))

(cond
  ((equal? command \"play\")
   (tone 440 1.0))
  ((equal? command \"stop\")
   (* 0.0 (tone 440 0.0)))
  (else
   (speech/say \"Command not recognized.\")))
```

*[needs: record, speech/listen, speech/say]*  
<!-- BUILD: record, STT, TTS -->

The system listens for \"play\" or \"stop\" and responds accordingly.

